snippet.title: Gmail of journalists in Myanmar said to be hacked
snippet.description: Google warns reporters in the Southeast Asian country that "state-sponsored attackers" possibly spied on their e-mails. The Myanmar government denies the allegation.

snippet.title: Google's Schmidt to preach Internet gospel in Myanmar
snippet.description: His controversial North Korea junket behind him, Eric Schmidt heads to a country that Reporters Without Borders last year listed as an "enemy of the Internet."

snippet.title: Cisco to open tech training academies in Myanmar
snippet.description: After joining Google, HP, Intel, and Microsoft in a delegation to the Southeast Asian country, Cisco pledges to set up training centers to help teach locals tech skills.

snippet.title: Ethnic fare for your fridge
snippet.description: Kimchi and Korean Meal magnet sets are a cute way to decorate your refrigerator and celebrate Korean cuisine

snippet.title: Myanmar or Burma? Apple's dictionary had an opinion
snippet.description: Language Log notes that Apple's Dictionary program (v. 1.02 running in Tiger) gave an interesting pronunciation for "Myanmar:" It's pronounced "Burma."

snippet.title: 20,000km undersea cable to link Singapore to Europe
snippet.description: The new 100Gbps fiber-optic link will open up international communications for 15 telecommunications companies and protect against severed cables or other problems.

snippet.title: Tom Perkins addresses his thorny '1 percent' comment
snippet.description: The outspoken venture capitalist elaborates on his controversial remarks about the rich and Nazi Germany during an interview in San Francisco.

snippet.title: China's Sina Weibo creates 'user contract,' increasing censorship
snippet.description: After government criticism and a temporary shutdown of Web comments, China's biggest microblogging site plans to introduce a "user contract" that could impede the free flow of information.

snippet.title: Old OS X malware used in increased attacks against Uyghur groups
snippet.description: An old vulnerability in Word for OS X is being used in increasing levels of attacks against ethnic groups in China.

snippet.title: Teenage mobile users do worry about privacy, says Pew
snippet.description: More than half of teens polled say they have rejected certain apps over privacy concerns, according to the Pew Research Center.
